From git@z Thu Jan  1 00:00:00 1970
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] RDMA/bnxt_re: Fix UBSAN shift and NULL deref for zero-depth RQ
From: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
Date: Tue, 01 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0600
Message-Id: <20260401-bnxt-fix-ubsan-hwq-v2@raithlin.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

After the QP creation refactor (patch 0002), bnxt_re_setup_qp_hwqs()
calls bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq() for both SQ and RQ unconditionally.
When the DV path creates a QP without an RQ (qprva==0), it zeroes
rq.max_wqe so get_depth() returns 0.

Two bugs result:

1. roundup_pow_of_two(0) in bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq triggers
   undefined behavior: fls_long(0 - 1) returns 64, producing
   1UL << 64.  UBSAN reports:
     shift exponent 64 is too large for 64-bit type 'long unsigned int'

2. bnxt_qplib_create_qp dereferences rq->hwq.pbl[PBL_LVL_0].pg_map_arr
   unconditionally when !qp->srq, causing a NULL pointer dereference
   when the RQ HWQ was never allocated.

Fix by:
- qplib_res.c: return 0 (success, empty HWQ) when both depth and
  aux_depth are zero; guard all roundup_pow_of_two() calls; default
  pgsize to PAGE_SIZE when uninitialized.
- ib_verbs.c: skip RQ HWQ allocation in setup_qp_hwqs when depth
  is zero.
- qplib_fp.c: guard the RQ PBL dereference in bnxt_qplib_create_qp
  with an rq->max_wqe check.

Signed-off-by: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c  |  2 ++
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_fp.c  |  8 +++++---
 drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c | 14 +++++++++++---
 3 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/ib_verbs.c
 static int bnxt_re_setup_qp_hwqs(...)
 {
 	...
 	/* RQ HWQ -- skip when depth is zero (DV QP
 	 * without receive queue). */
+	if (hwq_attr.depth) {
 		rc = bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq(&rq->hwq, &hwq_attr);
 		...
 		rq->hwq.pg_sz_lvl = pg_sz_lvl;
+	}
 	...
 }

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_fp.c b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_fp.c
--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_fp.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_fp.c
 int bnxt_qplib_create_qp(...)
 {
 	...
 	/* RQ */
 	if (!qp->srq) {
 		rq->dbinfo.flags = 0;
 		req.rq_size = cpu_to_le32(rq->max_wqe);
-		pbl = &rq->hwq.pbl[PBL_LVL_0];
-		req.rq_pbl = cpu_to_le64(pbl->pg_map_arr[0]);
-		req.rq_pg_size_rq_lvl = rq->hwq.pg_sz_lvl;
+		if (rq->max_wqe) {
+			pbl = &rq->hwq.pbl[PBL_LVL_0];
+			req.rq_pbl = cpu_to_le64(pbl->pg_map_arr[0]);
+			req.rq_pg_size_rq_lvl = rq->hwq.pg_sz_lvl;
+		}
 		...
 	}
 	...
 }

diff --git a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
--- a/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
+++ b/drivers/infiniband/hw/bnxt_re/qplib_res.c
 int bnxt_qplib_alloc_init_hwq(...)
 {
 	...
 	pg_size = hwq_attr->sginfo->pgsize;
 	hwq->level = PBL_LVL_MAX;

+	if (!hwq_attr->depth && !hwq_attr->aux_depth)
+		return 0;
+
+	if (!pg_size)
+		pg_size = PAGE_SIZE;
+
-	depth = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->depth);
-	stride = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->stride);
+	depth = hwq_attr->depth ?
+		roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->depth) : 0;
+	stride = hwq_attr->stride ?
+		roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->stride) : 0;
 	if (hwq_attr->aux_depth) {
 		aux_slots = hwq_attr->aux_depth;
-		aux_size = roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->aux_stride);
+		aux_size = hwq_attr->aux_stride ?
+			roundup_pow_of_two(hwq_attr->aux_stride) : 0;
 		...
 	}
 	...
 }
